
************ Install process for AZOrange on CentOS ************************

1) git clone https://github.com/JonnaStalring/AZOrange.git

2) ./install/prepareCentOS4AZO.sh 

3) In install dir: cp setup.ini.ubuntu.dev  setup.ini 

4) Adjust to system environment in setup.ini

5) In install directory: python install.py

6) The install.py script will fail because changes are needed to the OpenCV source code for it to compile. 

7) To make OpenCV compile: 
	Edit the file: orangeDependencies/src/opencv/include/opencv/ml.h
	Line 1434 change to:
        _inputs_val=cv::Mat()
        _outputs_val=cv::Mat()

8) Restart install.py without downloading OpenCV (comment out line 78 and 79 in install.py).


